project.projectDescription: This research contains Data of suicide population during 1985-2016 in two countries, With research on suicide as the response variable, we can tell the relation between suicide population and other indicators. Thus provide valuable inference to government preventing suicide.
project.dataDescription: Country: chr “Albania” “Antigua and Barbuda” Year: num 1985-2016 Gender: chr “Male” “Female” Suicide number: num GDP for the year: num GDP per capital: num Population: num Generation: chr “Silent” “Boomer” “X” “G.I” ”Z” “Millenials”
project.researchQuestion: Is there any difference in suicide number between generation? Is the difference driven by population?
project.conclusion: After adjusting for population F-statistic of generation is still significant 12.51>8.17>2.2 and become bigger. So there are more different generations. So it is not driven by populations.
